{"cards":[{"lines":[{"type":"title","text":"Lens equation"},{"type":"headline","text":"Interpretation of signs"}]},{"lines":[{"type":"title","text":"Magnification equation"},{"type":"headline","text":"  <math>    <mrow>      <mi>m<\/mi>      <mo>=<\/mo>      <mfrac linethickness=\"thin\">        <mrow>          <msub>            <mi>h<\/mi>            <mtext>i<\/mtext>          <\/msub>        <\/mrow>        <mrow>          <msub>            <mi>h<\/mi>            <mtext>o<\/mtext>          <\/msub>        <\/mrow>      <\/mfrac>      <mo>=<\/mo>      <mfrac linethickness=\"thin\">        <mrow>          <mtext>image\u00a0height<\/mtext>        <\/mrow>        <mrow>          <mtext>object\u00a0height<\/mtext>        <\/mrow>      <\/mfrac>    <\/mrow>  <\/math>"},{"type":"headline","text":"  <span class=\"math\">    <i>m<\/i> = magnification<\/span>"}]}],"definitions":[],"secText":["  <b>Essential Question: <\/b>  <b>    <br \/>  <\/b>How can we calculate the properties of thin lenses?","  <b>Enduring Understandings:<\/b>  <b>    <br \/>  <\/b>1. The reciprocal of the <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='21' data-topic='6' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>focal length<\/a> of a thin lens is equal to the sum of the reciprocal of the object distance and reciprocal of the image distance.<br \/>2. The <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='21' data-topic='6' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='0'>magnification<\/a> of an object can be calculated by dividing the image height by the object height or by dividing the negative of the image distance by the object distance.","  <b>Vocabulary: <\/b>  <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='21' data-topic='6' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='0'>magnification<\/a>","  <b>STEM Skills:<\/b>  <b>    <br \/>  <\/b>1. Review <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='2' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>object and image distance<\/a>.<br \/>2. Review <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='2' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>object and image height<\/a>.<br \/>3. Review <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='1' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='2'>focal length<\/a>."],"objNames":["wb_lens_mag_eq_concepts","wb_magnification_equation"]}